FBIS3-38477 "drweu023_l_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-023 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Feb 1994 SPAIN Gonzalez `Satisfied' With Provincial PSOE Congresses PM0202152094 Madrid YA in Spanish 28 Jan 94 p 22 PM0202152094 Madrid YA Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "Gonzalez Says That There Is Clear Desire for Renewal in PSOE"] [Excerpt] Madrid -- Prime Minister Felipe Gonzalez expressed Wednesday [26 January] his satisfaction at the outcome of the PSOE [Spanish Socialist Workers Party] provincial congresses which have been held, since they express a "clear desire" for renewal and integration. At a joint press conference with Finnish Prime Minister Esko Aho at the Moncloa Palace, the PSOE leader described as positive the outcome of those congresses, at which the delegates to the March federal summit were elected and at which the sum total of renewalists and integrationists defeated the Guerraists. Satisfied "The congresses clearly express the party's majority wishes; this is unequivocal," and represents "a clear desire for renewal, integration, and cohesion," said Gonzalez, who declared himself "satisfied" with the results. "Renewal and integration are what was put across at the provincial congresses," the prime minister stated, emphasizing that this lies "within the message which I have tried to convey with all due respect to the party, whose say it is right now." [passage omitted]
